DIRGE
The Flagon's Sentry — Maven's Quiet Answer
AP 16 (Master-tier band, 15-25) — player-legal build, itemized below
"Lanterns." / "Dirge."

Wiry Breton, crossbow across his knees, the barrel at the Ratway fork (Ch.20). The
Guild's outer security: he decides who passes, prices what they want, and forgets
nothing. When Maven finally assembles what she already holds on the Grelod kill
(factions/the black-briars, IV-V), Dirge is the hand she sends. He is not a duelist.
He is a verdict.

@web: dirge | kills-for | maven | Her Guild enforcer: when the Grelod fuse lights, Dirge is dispatched to kill the responsible Lantern(s). One shot, one exit.

=====================================================================
I. STAT BLOCK (d20; scores are his Target Numbers)
=====================================================================
Race: Breton (Dragonskin: once per adventure, half damage from one hostile spell)
Standing Stone: The Shadow (Shadow Form: once per adventure, perfectly invisible
  3 rounds or until hostile action — no roll)

Might: 8    Agility: 18    Magic: 5    Guile: 11
HP: 12      FP: 15         DR: 1 (Leather — Supple: Advantage on Sneak rolls)

He is deliberately GLASS. If the party ever pins him in the open, he dies like any
man — and he knows it, which is why no one has ever pinned him in the open.

THE AP-16 LEDGER (from a creation-legal base: Adept Archery; Apprentice Sneak,
Light Armor, One-Handed):
  Archery Adept->Expert 2, Expert->Master 3 ............ 5 AP
  Sneak Apprentice->Adept 1, ->Expert 2, ->Master 3 .... 6 AP
  Agility 17 -> 18 ..................................... 3 AP
  Resource Training: +2 FP, +2 HP ...................... 2 AP
  TOTAL ................................................ 16 AP

=====================================================================
II. GEAR
=====================================================================
Ebony Crossbow  | 18 damage | Piercing Bolt (ignores 2 DR), Long Range (Advantage
                  at furthest range), Reload (Minor Action per shot)
Paralysis Poison x2 | applied bolts: on hit, target makes a Might roll or is
                  Paralyzed, losing their next turn (Minor Action to apply)
Steel Dagger    | 4 damage  | Assassin's Blade (x3 damage on sneak-attack critical)
Leather Armor   | DR 1      | Supple: Advantage on Sneak

=====================================================================
III. HOW HE FIGHTS (once, from the dark, then gone)
=====================================================================
THE FIRST SHOT (the kill Maven pays for): from Hidden, at long range, poisoned bolt,
  Bullseye (9 FP).
  Deadly Aim (Adept Sneak): any attack from Hidden is an automatic Critical (x2).
  Bullseye (Master Archery): double damage (x2). Multipliers multiply:
  18 x 2 x 2 = 72 damage, ignoring 2 DR — plus the Paralysis rider on whatever
  survives. He spends this on the NAMED target only. Never on a bodyguard, never
  on an opportunity. Maven's ledger names one person at a time.
FP 15 IS THE DESIGN: Bullseye (9) + Vanish (6, Expert Sneak: re-hide while observed)
  = exactly 15 — one masterstroke and one exit. OR Invisibility (15, Master Sneak,
  3 rounds) as the approach. Never both. One perfect play per engagement; Shadow
  Form (free, once per adventure) is the emergency door.
IF THE SHOT DOESN'T KILL: he is already leaving. He does not duel, does not banter,
  does not finish wounded targets at melee range. A cornered Dirge negotiates —
  flatly, honestly — because Maven's ledger does not pay out to dead men.
CONTEST GAP: AP 16 vs the party's ~9-10 = gap of ~6 -> -5 to their TN on will-vs-will
  contests against him. Rarely relevant: he does not dominate anyone. He shoots them.

=====================================================================
IV. GM VOICE & HANDLING
=====================================================================
- Flat, patient, economical. He has never once raised his voice on the record and
  the reckoning is not the day he starts.
- THE TRADITION IS THE KNIFE: "Lanterns." / "Dirge." — the same exchange, the same
  tone, every visit since Ch.20. When the reckoning comes, open it with the exact
  same greeting in the exact same voice, in whatever unexpected place he has chosen.
  The table should understand what is happening from two words.
- He deploys ONLY when Maven's attention turns hostile and she assembles the fuse
  (the trigger, not the evidence — she already holds all the evidence). Until that
  day he is the toll-taker at the fork, and he nods, and they pass.
- Competence, not cruelty: he does not hate the Lanterns. He priced them the day
  they first walked down the stairs, same as everyone.
